This program creates an ArrayList of integers, adds
elements to it using the add() method,
and stores them dynamically. Finally, it prints
the elements in insertion order as [1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 11].

Note: ArrayList cannot hold primitive types like int, double, or char directly. we must use their wrapper classes instead:
-Use Integer instead of int
-Use Double instead of double
-Use Character instead of char